The convective heat transfer, in contrast, is assisted by a bulk flow of matter that transports heat from a point of high temperature to a point of low temperature. Convective heat transfer can occur in two ways, either through free convection, where fluid flow is caused by density variations in a stagnant medium, or through forced convection, where fluid flow is controlled and directed. The terms Q˙jconv\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
